OL,3,CBlind man 'daunted' every time he gets
OL,4,Con a bus
OL,6,F"To actually have that assurance of an
OL,7,Fannouncement, knowing that you're
OL,8,Fgoing to be secure and confident to
OL,9,Fget off where you need to go and not
OL,10,Fmiss your stop, really helps you to
OL,11,Frelax and think more positively about
OL,12,Fthe prospect of a journey rather than
OL,13,Fhaving to stress about it and plan a
OL,14,Flot in advance," Phillip explained.
